Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the orzo.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @Roasted Spice and Herb Blend{1%sachet} and @Plain Flour{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the @British Chicken Thighs{4} and toss to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken thighs flat in the pan. Fry until browned all over, ~{3-4%mins} each side.

Once the chicken is browned, transfer to a large #baking tray{}. Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When boiling, add the @Orzo{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{10%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @Olive Oil{for the orzo} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, trim the @Courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Return the (now empty) chicken pan to medium-high heat (no need to clean). Add another drizzle of oil if the pan is a little dry.

When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%mins} total. Turn only every couple of mins.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @Lemon{1} into wedges.

Once the courgette is charred, add the garlic and @Butter{10%grams}. Allow to melt, then toss to coat the courgette, ~{30%secs}. Remove from the heat.

In a large bowl, combine the @Pesto{32%grams}, half the lemon juice, a pinch of lemon zest and the @Olive Oil{1%tbsp for the dressing}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the cooked orzo and courgette to the dressing. Crumble in half the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%grams}. Toss to coat.

Taste and season with more salt, pepper and lemon juice if needed.

When the chicken is cooked, drizzle over the @Red Pepper Chilli Jelly{37%grams}. Turn to coat, then cut thinly widthways into 1cm slices.

Share the pesto orzo between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chicken. Drizzle over any leftover glaze from the tray.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese and lemon zest. Enjoy!